Koyeb Logo

Hi Ihunna,

Major news: Dockerfile deployments on high-performance microVMs are in general availability ( https://www.koyeb.com/blog/dockerfile-deployment-on-high-performance-microvms-is-ga )! You can now deploy any GitHub repository that contains a Dockerfile across all our locations worldwide.

Use it to deploy your APIs, full-stack applications, and workers at no extra cost. Read the full announcement ( https://www.koyeb.com/blog/dockerfile-deployment-on-high-performance-microvms-is-ga )¬†and check out how fast it is to deploy via a Dockerfile on the platform ( https://app.koyeb.com/ ):

( https://www.koyeb.com/blog/dockerfile-deployment-on-high-performance-microvms-is-ga )

Additionally, this week's changelog includes more features and improvements! Here is a rundown of everything new:

* Koyeb Organizations in the CLI
* New guide to Deploy Authorizer on Koyeb ( https://www.koyeb.com/tutorials/deploy-authorizer-to-handle-user-authentication-on-koyeb )
* Fixed display bug on new git deployment
* Koyeb at Infobip Shift's Conference ( https://twitter.com/yann_eu/status/1698649333317472720 )¬†and on the latest Cup o' Go podcast
episode ( https://cupogo.dev/episodes/slog-ging-through-a-mountain-of-go-news )
For more details about these updates, check out the full changelog #28 ( https://community.koyeb.com/t/changelog-28-deploy-dockerfiles-in-ga-organizations-in-the-cli-authorizer-x-koyeb-fixed-display-bug-and-more/744 )¬†update on the Koyeb Community.

Read the changelog ( https://community.koyeb.com/t/changelog-28-deploy-dockerfiles-in-ga-organizations-in-the-cli-authorizer-x-koyeb-fixed-display-bug-and-more/744 )

Missed Changelog #27 ( https://community.koyeb.com/t/changelog-27-workers-in-ga-zero-downtime-redeploys-billing-widget-api-credentials-and-improved-logs-experience/713 )¬†from last week? Native workers are in GA ( https://www.koyeb.com/blog/deploy-and-scale-high-performance-background-jobs-with-koyeb-workers )¬†, meaning you can deploy high-performance workers across 6 locations! üá∫üá∏ üá©üá™ üá´üá∑ üáØüáµ üá∏üá¨

One last thing, you might have heard that we are currently working on our Managed Postgres offering ( https://community.koyeb.com/t/managed-postgres-offering-user-testing/740 ). We are looking for early feedback on the design and experience.

Would like to partake in a quick remote user testing to share your feedback? Book a call ( https://calendly.com/kamil-dk0/managed-postgres-user-testing?month=2023-09 )¬†with our product designer, Kamil ( https://www.koyeb.com/blog/meet-kamil-product-designer-optimizing-dx ). Heads up: the number of spots is limited.

Wishing you a great week full of blazing-fast deployments!

Serverlessly,

Yann
